26:29.369 --> 26:36.580
And why did he veil his glory while having become like what?

26:37.101 --> 26:38.403
And John puts it this way.

26:38.443 --> 26:39.725
He dwelt among us.

26:39.946 --> 26:42.770
And he uses the word tabernacled.

26:43.106 --> 26:43.827
among us.

26:44.027 --> 26:51.117
That's another expression for the tent of meeting from your Old Testament stories.

26:51.177 --> 26:53.961
You remember the Old Testament tabernacle.

26:54.662 --> 27:07.859
It was a place where sinners could draw near to God in fellowship with God and communion with God even with a holy God and be welcomed and not cast away.

27:08.981 --> 27:12.946
It's where sinful men and sinful women and sinful boys and girls.

27:13.858 --> 27:19.285
could gather up around the one true holy God and be welcomed.

27:20.206 --> 27:26.054
The Tabernacle was the place where heaven and earth meet, where God and man meet.

27:27.455 --> 27:30.880
And John is saying, that's actually Jesus.

27:31.801 --> 27:42.034
The Tabernacle was a picture of and a promise of Jesus such that it is safe

27:42.498 --> 27:46.605
to come to God in all his holy righteousness.

27:48.368 --> 27:54.658
It is safe to come to God through Jesus and you are invited to do so.

27:54.678 --> 27:57.704
Now why did he have to take our flesh?

27:58.224 --> 28:08.722
Well, lots of reasons we'll look into next week, but of course so that he could die for our sins because the wages of sin is death and we have sinned.

28:09.314 --> 28:14.901
And so he took on our flesh so that he could stand in for us as a truly human being.

28:15.902 --> 28:18.285
Why was it required that he be God?

28:18.345 --> 28:22.610
Why do we need a mediator who is both God and man?

28:22.690 --> 28:27.156
Here, let me point you to the Westminster larger catechism question 38.

28:27.276 --> 28:28.577
Google it when you get home.

28:29.739 --> 28:35.105
It was required or requisite, but it was necessary that the mediator should be God.

28:35.185 --> 28:35.666
Why?

28:36.386 --> 28:48.943
Now listen to this that he might sustain and keep the human nature, his human nature, from sinking under the infinite wrath of God and the power of death.

28:50.505 --> 29:03.602
How did Christ upon a cross bearing shame and scoffing rude and saying, my God, my God, why have you forsaken me and suffering the

29:03.746 --> 29:06.151
just judgment of sinners in their place.

29:06.231 --> 29:17.755
How did Jesus in His humanity not once sin in anger, in wrath, in cursing that He should be thus cursed?

29:19.258 --> 29:24.850
Well, it was the humanity united to the divinity that sustained His humanity

29:25.506 --> 29:26.587
in that condition.

29:26.668 --> 29:30.793
Now that's not the larger catechism, I started preaching it, but you hear what I'm saying.

29:30.853 --> 29:36.521
It kept the human nature from sinking under the infinite wrath of God and the power of death.

29:36.581 --> 29:38.083
How did death not consume him?

29:39.365 --> 29:49.379
And also the catechism says to give worth and efficacy, worth and effectiveness so that it accomplished what it was supposed to.

29:50.760 --> 29:54.866
Worth an efficacy to his sufferings, his obedience, and his intercession.

29:55.874 --> 30:07.267
And so satisfy God's justice and procure his favor and purchase a peculiar people, his spirit to them, conquer all their enemies and bring them to everlasting salvation.

30:08.729 --> 30:17.639
It was so that he could guarantee you all the blessings of God that he had to be God and man in one person.

30:17.739 --> 30:23.986
So the great thing about Christmas, to put it in crass commercial terms,

30:24.578 --> 30:29.483
is not Black Friday where you get more for less with no money down.

30:30.564 --> 30:31.705
Buy now and pay later.

30:32.766 --> 30:34.507
That's not the great blessing of Christmas.

30:35.629 --> 30:53.906
The great thing about Christmas is that you can get all that God has promised to give with no money down, no money due, no payments owed because the Father has given you the gift of His Son and all things belong to Him

30:54.242 --> 31:01.789
and he shares all things with all who are united to him through faith in him.

31:01.969 --> 31:07.594
Put your hope, put your trust in him, and he is yours and you are his.

31:08.876 --> 31:15.081
So, dear Christians, rejoice and worship him.

31:16.062 --> 31:16.603
Let's pray.

31:17.984 --> 31:24.210
Father, thank you for the wonder of a baby born to a virgin

31:24.962 --> 31:36.574
raised and crucified and then raised from the dead when ascended and seated and coming again.

31:38.396 --> 31:44.822
We glory in and we boast in him and his work.

31:44.842 --> 31:51.209
May he be honored and glorified among us and may we be blessed by him in Jesus name.

31:52.210 --> 31:52.690
Amen.

31:53.314 --> 31:55.218
Amen, let's stand together and sing.

